# T5i repeatable native poller probe - 2026-05-23

Purpose: turn the native Pentagon poller blocker into a repeatable probe instead
of a one-off manual procedure.

## Script

Added scripts/probe-native-poller.mjs.

The script:

- reads the authenticated Pentagon session locally.
- discovers Theo and Maya from active_graph agent rows.
- discovers their shared conversation through conversation_participants.
- stops the external bridge unless --keep-bridge-running is passed.
- inserts a fresh Theo-to-Maya probe message.
- waits for the corresponding agent_triggers row.
- watches for native claim/completion and Maya ACK.
- restores the bridge in a finally path unless --no-restore is passed.
- exits non-zero when native polling does not complete the handoff.

## Discovery check

Command:

~~~text
node --check scripts/probe-native-poller.mjs
node scripts/probe-native-poller.mjs --keep-bridge-running --watch-seconds 1
~~~

Result:

~~~text
hash: T5I_NATIVE_POLLER_PROBE_20260523T132044Z
conversation_id: 0d996a94-45a6-4ef6-b8bd-45bc3f84d7e1
message_id: d4d96783-187f-4f83-a28c-0e8557dede2d
trigger_id: bc67946d-1597-48be-9088-40805d2da3a0
verdict: native_poller_still_blocked
bridge_before: running
~~~

This confirmed the script could discover the correct agents/conversation and
create/read the trigger path.

## Native-only bounded probe

Command:

~~~text
node scripts/probe-native-poller.mjs --watch-seconds 30
~~~

Result:

~~~text
hash: T5I_NATIVE_POLLER_PROBE_20260523T132150Z
conversation_id: 0d996a94-45a6-4ef6-b8bd-45bc3f84d7e1
message_id: 995505d3-f9e0-4fd1-b69c-30c641eb457d
trigger_id: 79e2cf07-0c2e-454e-a1ec-42ddb869faee
initial_claimed_at: null
final_claimed_at: null
final_completed_at: null
ack_count: 0
verdict: native_poller_still_blocked
bridge_restore_ok: true
~~~

Interpretation: message-to-trigger creation worked, but native Pentagon polling
did not claim or complete the target trigger and Maya produced no ACK inside the
bounded native-only window.

## Cleanup

The restored daemon did not claim the fresh pending trigger during the immediate
follow-up wait, so the exact trigger was processed explicitly through the bridge
to avoid leaving stale work queued:

~~~text
node scripts/pentagon-trigger-bridge.mjs \
  --trigger-id 79e2cf07-0c2e-454e-a1ec-42ddb869faee \
  --codex-timeout-ms 180000

cleanup_exit: 0
status: completed
persisted_message_id: d8f03355-8584-4771-be25-ef97639695d0
completed_at: 2026-05-23T13:23:22.002463+00:00
stderr_tail: empty
~~~

## Verdict

Native Pentagon handoff activation remains red. The failure is now repeatably
testable from a repo script, and the bridge cleanup path remains available and
auditable.
